<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{x}-{3}{y}=-{11}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}-{y}={57}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{7},-{8}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of --7. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle--\frac{{7}}{{5}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{-{7}}}{{5}}{\left({5}{x}+-{3}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{-{7}}}{{5}}{\left(-{11}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left(-{7}\right)}{x}+-{4.2}{y}=-{15.4}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}-{y}={57}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5.2}{y}={41.6}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{41.6}}{{-{{5.2}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{8}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{x}+-{3}{\left(-{8}\right)}=-{11}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{x}+{\left({24}\right)}=-{11}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{x}=-{11}-{\left({24}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{x}=-{35}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{35}}{{5}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{7}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{7},-{8}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

